This paper discusses the use of random Fourier features in machine learning, which is a common technique in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the error bounds and approximation error of the method, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of random Fourier features also involves numerical analysis and optimization, which are covered by the categories of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of random Fourier features in machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
